18 Feb 2019 16:42






I'll stuff my thoughts on the collapsible below.

+thoughts

-thoughts


First off, I think your clinical tone is spot on, and there's not much left to me to complain about. The sentences are clear, and the overall structure of the article has been pulled off well. Also, the image is pretty nice, so good job on that. Now, to the whole

I'm not really sure of what the point of the anomaly is? Sure, ToasterDoot created them to cause trouble to the Foundation, but even then I didn't understand the reasoning behind it previously cataloging them as anomalous. People apparently thought that seeing them caused unrelated symptoms? I don't think there's enough buildup on that, and it should be explained further.

The chat conversation feels realistic to me, and their personalities are clearly presented, but it's too short to make me care about the characters and their relationships. I felt like I only catched a brief glimpse of a bigger article, and I don't really understand what exactly is going on in the lives of the GAW group; I'm not sure on how to remedy that, but maybe extending the logs and including further explanation could help with it?




I'm ultimately no-voting here. I personally think you've took a hold of a good concept basis here, and you've included good imagery, but the downside I see is its vagueness and lack of a build-up.















