18 Feb 2019 17:06






Thanks for your critique! I've decided to remove the idea of the item being previously deemed anomalous, which includes the removal of the archived procedures. I added and changed a small amount of the procedures to try and express that 1. Not everyone who sees the anomaly immediately thinks they have the disease which I've expressed in the recovery and 2. that people who think they have the disease are people who are in an environment where things are anomalous. In the recovery, people at the hospital only reported that the posters existed, not that they had the disease. The only ones who have claimed to be affected so far are those in a setting where it could be anomalous for all they know.

As for the chat logs, I only meant for this to be a brief glimpse into their world. A quick little distraction so that Toaster could move apartments without being hassled by the Foundation. I feel that extending the logs would only make the article more drawn out.

Again, your advice was really helpful and I'm happy that you enjoyed the article!







