18 Feb 2019 22:47






Thanks for the feedback! I understand why you believe this wouldn’t initially be considered anomalous, but I still feel it warrants an EX designation. Why I believe that this would be considered an EX is because of its close relation to other anomalous activity. In addition, it was thought to possibly harbor cognitohazardous or otherwise mind-affecting properties when it was first discovered.

The logs themselves support the idea of it being at least created by an anomalous humanoid involved with a known GoI. Things like this have been used in other Explained SCPs like SCP-1094-EX where the only perceived anomalous property was that it looked like a big eyeball. To hopefully clear this up, I’ve added that the object class for the posters was pending, similarly to 1094-EX. Again, thanks for the clear and concise feedback, I really do appreciate it.





